content.description: Monica and Chandler’s, Monica and Chandler are getting ready to go on their honeymoon. Monica is entering from the bedroom.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hey! Babe! Aren’t you excited we’re going on our honeymoon?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Yeah I am!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Bermuda, Bahama, come on pretty mama …

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: That’s right. Get it out of your system while we’re alone.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah! Have a great honeymoon!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I’d better go pack.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Oh no, I already packed. The only thing I couldn’t find though was your Speedo.
(Joey looks at him, Phoebe tries not to smile, and Chandler is shocked.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: A Speedo? Uh, I don’t have a Speedo. I’m gonna go pack my regular long bathing suit. (Goes into the bedroom.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh good you’re still here!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I want to tell you to have a good honeymoon! (Hugs Monica.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Thank you.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: And I also wanted you guys to know that I am telling the father today. (They all look at her expectantly) What? What? What?
(Pause.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: We know its Ross!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: How?! How do you know?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: It was his sweater, but—Oh my God!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh, I so wanted Ross to know first, but I’m so relieved you guys know.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: This is so great! And I’m gonna be your baby’s aunt!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I know! (They hug.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Me too! (Joins the hug.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I’m gonna be an uncle! Come here! (He joins the hug.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: You’re all gonna be aunts and uncles.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Yeah, but I’m the only one related by blood.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay. Great! So now that you guys all know you can help me. Give me some advice on how I’m gonna tell Ross!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Well, what were you gonna say?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Well I was gonna tell him that I’m-I’m gonna have the baby and he can be as involved as he wants.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Well that, that sounds good.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah but how do I start? I mean, what’s-what’s the first thing that I say? (They all pause to think.) Okay great! Thanks. (She starts to leave.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hey! Good luck!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah, bye.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Bye.
(Rachel exits.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hey, what was that all about?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Well I guess there is no harm in telling you now, Rachel and Ross are gonna have a baby.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: What?! I didn’t even know that—Why didn’t you tell me?! (Pause) Why am I talking like this?!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: I didn’t think you could keep it a secret.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: What?! (Normal voice) I am an excellent secret keeper. I have kept all of our secrets.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What secrets?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh no-no Joey, I am not going to tell you because I am an excellent secret keeper.
(The girls walk away.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: You’ll tell me later?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: You already know.

content.description: Joey and Rachel’s, Joey and Phoebe are entering.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh, it’s so romantic to send people off on their honeymoon.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Y’know, Monica and Chandler are married. Ross and Rachel are having a baby. Maybe you and I should do something.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: All in good time my love. All in good time. Oh shoot! I left my guitar in their apartment. Well you can let me in later.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I don’t have a key, they took mine to give to you.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: What?! They took mine to give to you!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Why would they take away our keys?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Maybe they don’t trust us.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No that’s not it. They let me keep my key the last time they were out of town.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: You mean the time you broke the ketchup bottle and cleaned it up with Monica’s guest towels?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey, I washed those!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: No you didn’t.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah that didn’t sound like me.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well, what am I gonna do? I really need my guitar!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah, I have stuff in there too.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: What stuff?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Monica’s chicken parm! I’ll take care of it. (He picks up the phone) Hey Mr. Treeger, it’s Joey Tribbiani. Listen, I need to get into Monica and Chandler’s apartment. It’s an emergency. (Listens) Uhh, gas leak! Yeah oh, and bring garlic bread. (Hangs up.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Did Rachel find you?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No why?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh she was looking for you.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh well, I guess I’ll catch up with her later.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well, she really wanted to talk to you now.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah, it seemed pretty important.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh no.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I think I might know what this is about.
(Phoebe and Joey trade looks)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Really?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah. Uh, uh we promised we weren’t gonna tell anybody this but uh, about a month ago Rachel and I slept together.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: And?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Wow! I thought you would be a little more shocked.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh sorry. (Shocked) And?!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well, we-we said we’d just do it that one time but, but now I think she may wanna start things up again.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah, I don’t think that’s what it is.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Why? What-what else could it be?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh wow, I don’t feel well.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I’m telling you. I’m telling you. That’s what it is. No wonder she was looking at me all funny during the wedding. She didn’t say anything to you?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Maybe it’s something you ate?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Please, just-just, just go and talk to Rachel.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah, I guess I should. (Starts to leave.) Man, y’know what I have to realize? Maybe I’m just not the type of guy women can have just one night with. Y’know, they-they always seem to want a little bit more. I should remember that. (He pauses and then exits.)

content.description: The Airport Ticket Counter, Monica and Chandler are standing in line behind another couple kissing who are next in line to be served.

content.speaker: Ticket Agent
content.text: Next?
(The kissing couple doesn’t move.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: They’re kissing let’s just go around them.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh honey, leave them alone, they’re in love.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: I’m in love too! But in an orderly fashion.

content.speaker: Ticket Agent
content.text: Next?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hi! Can you do that and walk? ‘Cause she said, “Next.”
(The couple moves up to the counter.)

content.speaker: Woman
content.text: Sorry. We didn’t hear you; we’re on our honeymoon.

content.speaker: Ticket Agent
content.text: Oh, let me see what I can do. (Checks the computer) There are some first class seats available.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Did you hear that?! They bumped them up to first class because they are on their honeymoon! Come on! Let’s act like we’re on our honeymoon.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: We are on our honeymoon.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Grab my ass!

content.speaker: Ticket Agent
content.text: Next?
(They go up to the counter.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hi, sorry. I almost didn’t hear you, because y’know I’m just so in love with my new husband. We’re on our honeymoon.

content.speaker: Ticket Agent
content.text: Congratulations. Okay, Mr. Bing you’ll be in 25J and Mrs. Bing you’ll be in 25K.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Oh no, you see we’re on our honeymoon. So umm, can you do your little thing and bump us up to first class?

content.speaker: Ticket Agent
content.text: I’m sorry, all our first class seats are taken. That couple got the last two.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: You see, if we’d gone around them like I said, we—She would’ve given us those tickets. Damnit!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: 25J and K, any chance those aren’t together?

content.description: [Scene: Joey and Rachel’s, Phoebe and Joey are playing Rock ‘em, Sock ‘em Robots.]

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I still can’t believe they took away my key. You trust me with yours.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Of course I do! And I’m gonna give it back to you as soon as they’re done with it at the key shining place.
(They hear a knocking sound coming from the hallway and go to investigate.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What the hell is that?
(They go into the hallway and see Mr. Treeger watching one of New York’s bravest breakdown Monica and Chandler’s door with an ax.]

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Treeger, what are you doing?

content.speaker: Mr. Treeger
content.text: You said there was a gas leak in here.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well why don’t you use your key?

content.speaker: Mr. Treeger
content.text: Because by the time I find it on this thing (Holds up a huge key ring with a thousand keys on it), the whole place might have exploded. If that happens at another building that I manage, people are gonna start asking questions. (To the fireman) Come on! Hurry up.
(With a final swing the door gives way.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh! We could have done that.

content.description: The Airport, Chandler and Monica are following the previous couple through a tiny hallway that proves this is a set on a sound stage and not an actual airport, and see them enter the first class lounge.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Look at that! Look at that! They’re going into the first class lounge! Do you know what they have in there?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: No.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Me neither! We have to get in! (She runs through the door with Chandler in tow.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Just act like you belong.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Oh my God! Oranges!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Shh! (To the guy behind the counter) Nice to see you again. (They tries to walk past him.)

content.speaker: Airline Employee
content.text: Uh sir, may I see your tickets please?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Yes, of course. (Shows him the tickets.)

content.speaker: Airline Employee
content.text: I’m sorry, would you move your thumb? I can’t see the seat number.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh that’s all right, I have it memorized. It’s 1A.

content.speaker: Airline Employee
content.text: Sir, this is not a first class ticket. I’m sorry.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Apology accepted. Excuse us. (They try to enter again.)

content.speaker: Airline Employee
content.text: Sir! I’m afraid I’m gonna have to ask you to leave.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Fine. (Starts to walk away then she runs over and grabs an orange before she exits.) Go! Go! Go!

content.description: The Hallway Outside Ross’s Apartment, Ross is walking towards his apartment and sees Rachel sitting in front of the door.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hi!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hi.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hi. (He helps her up.) Umm, I think there’s something that we really need to talk about.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I think we do. Why don’t we go inside? (They go inside.) Look uh, I know why you’re here.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: You do?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah, and to save you from any embarrassment umm, I think maybe I should talk first.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Okay. (He sits her down in a chair.) Uh, Ross and Rachel. Rachel and Ross. That’s been one heck of a see-saw hasn’t it?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I mean look, that-that one night we had was fun and…and certainly passionate, but don’t you think it’s better if we just stayed friends?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Seriously. What?!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Okay. Okay. Y’know what? If you want to, we can do it one more time. I mean I’d-I’d be okay with that. In fact, I have some time right now.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay, y’know what? Can I, can I talk now?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh sure. (He sits on the apothecary table and touches her hand.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I’m pregnant. (Ross stops.) Ross? (Ross is staring off into space.) Ross? (Ross is still frozen) Okay, whenever you’re ready. (Sits back and opens her magazine.) And you’re the father by the way—but you got that…

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Can I get you some water?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I’m good. I’m good.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Ross, there is no pressure on you. Okay? I mean you can as involved as you want. (Ross nods.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah, I need uh… I’m just—I don’t know—I don’t understand, umm, how this happened? We-we used a condom.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I know. I know, but y’know condoms only work like 97% of the time.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What? What? What?!! Well they should put that on the box!!!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: They do!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No they don’t!!! (He runs to the bedroom to check and returns with his box of condoms.) Well they should put it in huge black letters!!!!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay Ross come on let’s just forget about the condoms.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh well I may as well have!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Listen, y’know what? I was really freaked out too when I found out…

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Freaked out? Hey no, I’m not freaked out! I’m indignant ! As a consumer !

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Y’know what? Let’s, let’s talk later.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No! No! I want to talk now! Okay? I—In fact, (picks up the phone) I am going to talk to the president of the condom company!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay, y’know maybe I should come back… (Starts to leave.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Shh! Shh! Shh!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah I’ll press 1! (Presses one which allows Rachel to escape.)

content.description: Monica and Chandler’s, Mr. Treeger has finished inspecting Monica and Chandler’s apartment.

content.speaker: Mr. Treeger
content.text: I’ve looked everywhere. There’s no gas leak.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Huh. So then I can heat this up? (Goes and does so.)

content.speaker: Mr. Treeger
content.text: Anyway uh, I’ll get moving on that new door.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh great! And listen, could you do us a favor and not tell Chandler and Monica about this? ‘Cause y’know umm, they don’t-they don’t have any kids of their own and-and this door was like a child to them.

content.speaker: Mr. Treeger
content.text: Well I’m gonna have to put on a new lock, they’ll find out anyway.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh no.

content.speaker: Mr. Treeger
content.text: Whoa! This looks like an all day job, I’ll have to cancel my yoga class. (Ross walks up.) Hey Ross!
content.parenthetical: measures the top of the doorframe

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hi.

content.speaker: Mr. Treeger
content.text: Could you tell Jasmine that I won’t make it to yoga class today?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Sure.

content.speaker: Mr. Treeger
content.text: Namaste. (Bows.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Namaste. (Bows.)
(Treeger leaves and Ross notices the door.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh my God! What happened to the door?!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: So it’s noticeable huh?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Look, is Rachel here? I really need to talk to her.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Didn’t you two already talk?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah but uh… Okay, okay look you guys know that Rachel and I slept together, but there’s something else. (Pause) Rachel’s pregnant.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh my God!!! I can’t believe that!!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Holy mother of God!!!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: With my child.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: That is brand new information!!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: You already know don’t you?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: A little bit.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: How are you doing?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Okay. Okay. I mean I’ll be okay. It’s just I don’t think I handled it very well.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Well, what did you say to her?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Nothing. But the complaint department at the condom company got an earful. And then when I turned around she was gone.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh Ross.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: But hey, in my defense I-I just found out condoms are like only 97% effective.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I gotta go find her.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Whoa! Hey! Whoa!! Hold up! Are you serious?! So like 3% of the time they don’t even work?! Huh? They should put that on the box!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Evidently they do.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What?! (Grabs his condoms from his pocket and looks.)

content.description: The Atlantis Resort, Chandler and Monica are arriving to check in, but are behind the couple from before again.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: I can’t believe we’re here.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh you’ve got to be kidding me.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: What? (Monica sees the first couple and gasps.)

content.speaker: Front Desk Clerk
content.text: As a wedding gift to you, the hotel would like to give you the honeymoon suite.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: No!! You have been screwing us all day!

content.speaker: Man
content.text: Who are you?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: We’re you just ten seconds later!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Yeah! You already got the first class tickets; you got the lounge! I mean we should get free stuff too! I mean you’re not the only ones on your honeymoon!

content.speaker: Woman
content.text: Well you can have the suite if you want. We don’t care about where we stay. We’re here to celebrate our love together. We don’t have to get free stuff. We just want to be together.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: We need the stuff.
content.parenthetical: looks at Monica then at them

content.description: Monica and Chandler’s, Joey is on the phone and Phoebe is watching him.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey Monica it’s Joey. Listen uh, Phoebe and I smell gas comin’ from your apartment.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: What? Are you serious?! (To Chandler) Joey smells gas!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: What else is new?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah and we’d go check it out, but you took away our keys.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Well do something! Get in there!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: How? I guess I could break down your door.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Yeah! Do that!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: And-and you won’t blame us for any damage? (Gives Phoebe a thumbs up.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: No! (Pause) Are you doing it?! I don’t hear anything! Come on!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Uh, okay I’ll-I’ll-I’ll break it down. (He hands the phone to Phoebe, gets up, picks up a chair, and starts banging it on the floor.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh hey hi, he’s doing it. He’s breaking down the door. (The chair breaks in half.) Okay, we’re in. (She hangs up the phone.)

content.description: A doctor’s office, Rachel is on an examining table with her legs in the stirrups.

content.speaker: Nurse
content.text: Okay Rachel, are you comfortable?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: If I said I was, would you judge me?

content.speaker: Nurse
content.text: The doctor will be here in a minute to do your sonogram.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay. (The nurse exits.) Oh man, I swear if they sold these at Pottery Barn …
(There’s a knock on the door and Ross enters.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hi!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hi!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Uh we-we need to talk.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Uh-uh-uh, right now? Because I’ve kinda got an el fresco situation going on over here.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Please, please I want to apologize for the way I acted earlier today.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay Ross that’s fine, but can you please stand near my head?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What? Oh yeah. (He moves next to her head.) I’m sorry. I mean I-I think I went a little crazy. I mean I was thinking about myself when I (Wanders towards Rachel’s feet) really—I should have been thinking about you Rach…

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay. Head Ross! Head Ross! Head Ross!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Right! Right! I just—I want you to know that I’m going to be there through this whole thing, okay? Okay? The doctor’s appointments, the uh, the Lamaze classes, uh baby-proofing the apartment—Although we could probably worry about that ‘til after we get married.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What married?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well yeah, I think we should get married.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What, because that’s your answer to everything?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No, because that’s the right thing to do.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah, maybe if you’re in love. But Ross, we are not in love, are we?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No but…but still you can’t possibly do this alone.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Excuse me?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Come on Rach, you can’t even eat alone in a restaurant.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What?!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I’m just saying if you can’t eat by yourself, how do you expect to have a baby by yourself?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I can too eat by myself!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: When have you ever?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: When certain people leave the table and I am not finished!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well certain other people take two hours to eat a bowl of soup!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh please, you inhale your food!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I grew up with Monica! If you didn’t eat fast you didn’t eat!!

content.speaker: Dr. Long
content.text: Am I interrupting?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh no Dr. Long, please come in. This is Ross, he is the father.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: But not the husband, because evidently she can do this alone.

content.speaker: Dr. Long
content.text: Huh. Nice to meet you. I’ll get started on this.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I don’t know why you can’t admit that you need me.
content.parenthetical: To Rachel, standing by her feet

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I do need you! I need you to stand near my head!

content.speaker: Dr. Long
content.text: Okay, everything looks good. Here it is on the screen. (We see Ross and Rachel looking at the screen.) Here is your uterus. And right here is your baby.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh my God.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Wow. There it is, I see it.

content.speaker: Dr. Long
content.text: Congratulations. I’ll give you two a minute.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Thank you.
(Dr. Long exits and Rachel starts to cry.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Pretty amazing huh?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I don’t see it!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What? What?!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I can’t see it!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: You-you just said that you did!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I know, I lied! I didn’t want her to think I was a terrible mother! I can’t even see my own baby!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh sure, come here! (Sits her up) Sure you can! Uh, look come here look, (rolls the machine closer) it’s-it’s-it’s, it’s right there (Points).

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh. Oh, it’s beautiful. I see it now.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Do you really?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: No, I don’t see it!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Come on! Come on! Here, okay-okay, you see this? (Points) This tiny thing that looks like a peanut?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Sweetie that’s it.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: That’s it? Well I saw that! Ohh-ohh-oh, thank you.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: You’re welcome.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Wow! I can’t believe that’s our baby.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah, that’s our baby.

content.description: Joey and Rachel’s, Joey and Phoebe are there as Rachel and Ross return from the doctor’s appointment.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hi.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Hey! So how was the doctor?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh, everything went great.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Good.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh hey, show them the picture of your uterus.
(She does so.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I don’t see the baby. Where is it?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh no, I know I couldn’t see it either at first, but it’s right umm… (Starts to cry) Ross, I lost it again.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh. (He takes the picture and hugs her.
